able Cape Conservation Area|Table Cape]] and [[Circular Head]]<ref name="eas-tas">http://oceans1.customer.netspace.net.au/tas-main.html Shipwrecks of Tasmania</ref> |- valign="top" | ||''Amelia J.''|| style="text-align:center;"|1920|| somewhere around the [[Furneaux Group]]<ref name="eas-tasfurn" >http://oceans1.customer.netspace.net.au/furneaux-main.html Furneaux Group Shipwrecks</ref> |- valign="top" | || [[Argo (1806 ship)|''Argo'']] || style="text-align:center;"|1814 || somewhere off the coast<ref name="eas-tas" /> |- valign="top" | ||''Awarau''|| style="text-align:center;"|1891 ||somewhere off [[Macquarie Island]]<ref name="eas-mac" >http://oceans1.customer.netspace.net.au/macquarie-main.html Macquarie Island Shipwrecks</ref> |- valign="top" | ||''Celestia''|| style="text-align:center;"|1887 || somewhere between [[Russell, New Zealand]] and [[Hobart]]<ref name="eas-tas" /> |- valign="top" | ||''Chris''|| style="text-align:center;"|1903 || somewhere between Hobart and [[Adventure Bay, Tasmania|Adventure Bay]]<ref name="eas-tas" /> |- valign="top" | ||''City of Hobart''|| style="text-align:center;"|1873 || somewhere between Hobart and Blackman's Bay<ref name="eas-tas" /> |- valign="top" | ||''Despatch''|| style="text-align:center;"|1826 || somewhere off Cape Pillar<ref name="eas-tas" /> |- valign="top" | ||''Elizabeth Radcliff''|| style="text-align:center;"|1850 || <ref name="eas-tas" /> |- valign="top" | ||''Fleetwing''|| style="text-align:center;"|1876 || <ref name="eas-tas" /> |- valign="top" | ||''John Leslie Griffiths''|| style="text-align:center;"|1880 || somewhere around King Island<ref name="eas-tasking">{{cite web|url=http://oceans1.customer.netspace.net.au/king-main.html|title=KING ISLAND - MAINFRAME|first=Peter|last=Stone|date=|website=oceans1.customer.netspace.net.au|accessdate=31 May 2018}}</ref> |- valign="top" | ||''Louisa''|| style="text-align:center;"|1882 ||somewhere around Fortescue Bay<ref name="eas-tas" /> |- valign="top" | ||''Omega''|| styl